result.formatted_address: 76 Wharf Rd, North Point, Hong Kong
result.name: Kambo Restaurant

reviews.text:
Local and typical HK style dishes, offering hotpot at night as well.

Not compromising food quality with very good value for money.

Shop owner is a HK couple, they are nice and friendly.

Shop floor is small but organized, clean and neat with high efficiency service. Recommended!
有很多菜式，有中式西式，晚上也有火鍋! 湯都很好, 下午來的時候會有杯潤喉雪梨水, 有別於其他店舖, 很有心~
很多不同選擇，中式西式都有！店面乾淨
食物都唔差，有水準，真材實料。
食物質素不錯，菜式選擇多

reviews.text: I‘ve never eaten at the canteen, but their bakery honestly makes the best buns hands down!!! The egg tarts are also really good depending on which pastry chef is there.
As the name suggests it is a cantina. Clean, fast and buget friendly!
出前一丁+ beff satay and fried egg is not bad. A filling meal!
Worst of all! Price is not high and it needs to be cheap to maintain business.
Classic HK style food & drinks with very reasonable price!
